{
  "_comment": "Phase 6B — preloaded queries for the pokemon-qs Query Suggest model. Three categories balanced for how real users search a Pokédex: ~100 species names (the bulk of organic traffic), ~30 type/generation/category filters (one-word taxonomy queries), ~20 natural-language questions (what RGA-grounded search is designed for). All entries are lowercased — Coveo normalizes case at training time but consistent input avoids any tokenizer quirks. Sorted alphabetically within each group for git-diff friendliness as we add or remove entries over time. Uploaded to the model via scripts/ml/seed_query_suggest.sh; the script reads .queries (flat list) and ignores .description / category arrays — those are documentation for humans.",
  "_format": {
    "description": "Coveo's Default Queries API accepts a flat string list. We surface the category breakdown as separate arrays for readability, but seed_query_suggest.sh concatenates them into the .queries field that gets uploaded.",
    "category_counts_target": {
      "names": 100,
      "type_and_generation": 30,
      "natural_language_questions": 20
    }
  },
